<TITLE> Four BIWTA, BSC vessels up for auction </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  The government will auction off two vessels of the inland transport authority and two of Bangladesh Shipping Corporation, shipping minister Shajahan Khan told parliament on Monday. "The government has decided in principle to sell two BIWTA (Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Authority) inspection vessels  Sonartori and Sonarkheya  through auction," he said in reply to a question by Pirojpur-3 constituency MP Anwar Hossain. Answering another question by Brahmanbaria-4 MP Md Shah Alam, he said two ships  MV Banglar Gourab and MV Banglar Urmi  under state-run BSC would be sold out as they are no longer viable to operate. The minister said tender have also been floated to auction off two ships and four pontoons of Mongla Port Authority. To a question by Comilla-8 MP Nasimul Alam Chowdhury, he said the government is procuring three dredgers soon. The purchase will be made after a gap of 35 years. Another 17 dredgers will be procured by 2015, he added. He said the government would procure four sea trucks and a 500-passenger ship for BIWTC (Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Corporation).
